{
  "id" : 733,
  "songNumber" : 121,
  "title" : "THEY COME FROM THE EAST AND WEST",
  "language" : "english",
  "capo" : 0,
  "bpm" : 0,
  "timeSignature" : "4/4",
  "hashtags" : [ ],
  "sections" : [ {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "VERSE 1",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "They come from the East and West,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 5
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "They come from the lands afar,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 19
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 26
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "To feast with the King, to dine as His guest;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 3
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 27
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "How blessed these pilgrims are!",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 21
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 27
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Beholding His hallowed face",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 2
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 23
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Aglow with light divine;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 1
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 19
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Blest partakers of His grace,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 9
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 23
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "As gems in His crown to shine.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 15
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "Since Jesus has set me free,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 6
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 23
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "I'm happy as heart can be;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 23
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "No longer I bear the burden of care,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 21
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "His yoke is so sweet to me.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 15
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 24
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "My soul was as black as night,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 15
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "But darkness has taken flight;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 17
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Now I shout the victory,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 6
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 16
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "For Jesus has set me free.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 21
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "I look on the great white throne,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 14
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Before it the ransom'd stand;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 2
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "No longer are tears, no sorrow is known",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 24
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Nor death in that goodly land.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 18
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "My Saviour has gone before,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 3
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 22
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Preparing the way for me;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 3
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 22
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Soon we'll meet to part no more",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 11
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Thru time or eternity.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 5
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 14
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "The gates of that holy place",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Stand open by night and day;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 6
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 24
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "O look to the Lord who \"giveth more grace,\"",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 23
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Whose love has prepared the way",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 6
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 18
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "A home in those mansions fair",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 2
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 19
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "His hand hath reserved for all,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 16
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "For the wedding feast prepare,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 8
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 25
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Obeying the gracious call.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 1
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 12
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 21
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "Oh, Jesus is coming soon,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 20
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Our trials will then be o'er.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 24
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "What if our Lord this moment should come.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 22
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "For those who are free from sin?",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 18
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Then would it bring you joy,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 5
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 24
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Or sorrow and deep despair?",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 21
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "When our Lord in glory comes,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 9
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 23
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "We'll meet Him up in the air.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 15
      } ]
    } ]
  } ]
}